  "_e2eLivePhasesDoc": "Ordered live-e2e phase skeleton the T10/T11 harness MUST run VERBATIM and IN ORDER for every connector. Source of truth = the canonical 'Integration Major Enhancement — Test Plan' §1→§7 (HANDOFF.md, mirrored from plan.md §14/§15); reference implementation = packages/Integration/connectors/test/ (the HubSpot live-test framework). floor-check iterates this list exactly as it iterates `slots`: every APPLICABLE phase must appear in the ladder's T10/T11 `livePhaseLog`, in this declared `order`, with per-test NL+JSON+pass/fail evidence (§6). Per-connector adaptation: the agent runs the applicable SUBSET (pull-only connectors skip push/bidirectional cells; no-watermark connectors run content-hash/keyset in place of the watermark cell), but the SKELETON + ORDERING is FIXED and any skipped phase/cell MUST carry a logged `skipReason` (no silent omission). §7 dual-dialect is MANDATORY: every applicable phase runs once on SQL Server, then identically on Postgres.",
  "e2eLivePhases": [
    {
      "id": "E2E.Env",
      "order": 0,
      "phaseRef": "§1 Environment Setup & Bring-up",
      "tier": "T10",
      "applicability": "always",
      "dualDialect": false,
      "requires": "Empty DB provisioned; mj migrate -> mj sync push -> mj codegen (in order) on this branch; mjapi + mjexplorer built and started; GQL API key obtained WITHOUT reading/exposing it (§0); initial Company record created.",
      "evidence": "Per-step NL statement + JSON (migrate/sync/codegen exit summaries, server-up confirmation, Company row id) + pass/fail."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2E.PhaseA",
      "order": 1,
      "phaseRef": "§2 Phase A — Integration & Metadata",
      "tier": "T10",
      "applicability": "always",
      "dualDialect": false,
      "requires": "Create CompanyIntegration record; link credential + connection-test via the broker (never expose the value, §0); RefreshMetadata pulls all custom tables, custom columns (on existing + custom tables), absent table metadata, and watermark info; LLM/statistics PK-inference runs per hard-key IO with results in additionalSchemaInfo.json; ApplyAllBatch over all selectable tables; subscription output inspected; structured end-of-phase report produced.",
      "evidence": "NL + JSON for each: connection-test result, RefreshMetadata diff (tables/columns/watermark), PK-classify verdicts, ApplyAllBatch map counts, the structured Phase-A report + pass/fail."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2E.PhaseB",
      "order": 2,
      "phaseRef": "§3 Phase B — Sync Testing (2^N matrix)",
      "tier": "T10",
      "applicability": "always-skeleton-applicable-cells",
      "dualDialect": false,
      "requires": "The combinatorial 2^N matrix; run every APPLICABLE cell — never shortcut, but a pull-only connector logs its push/bidirectional cells as skipped-with-reason, a no-watermark connector substitutes content-hash/keyset for the watermark cell. Sub-phases run in order 3.1->3.8.",
      "subPhases": [
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_1", "order": 1, "ref": "3.1 Change detection & efficiency", "requires": "watermark-first then full/rest pass + no-watermark path; timestamp-watermark incremental; content-hash/Merkle actually avoids redundant work; keyset pagination — restart the API mid-sync and confirm from logs it resumes." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_2", "order": 2, "ref": "3.2 Sync directions & write paths", "requires": "inbound; bidirectional (enumerate conflict, echo/loopback, simultaneous-both-sides, ordering); write-backs; watermark fallback save (persisted even on fallback path). Push/bidirectional cells skip-with-reason for pull-only connectors." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_3", "order": 3, "ref": "3.3 Identity & idempotency", "requires": "duplicate records -> no duplication / correct dedupe; re-run/replay stays idempotent." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_4", "order": 4, "ref": "3.4 Deletes & tombstoning", "requires": "delete + tombstone on DISPOSABLE test records only (§0); never touch users/owners/real records." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_5", "order": 5, "ref": "3.5 Schema drift", "requires": "source-side columns removed mid-stream handled gracefully; local-side columns removed -> same scrutiny; treat both as possibly adversarial; exercise other source-side mutations beyond column removal." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_6", "order": 6, "ref": "3.6 DAG", "requires": "DAG ordering follows the agreed contract — tested deeply, not superficially (second-layer/association tables non-empty when upstream has data)." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_7", "order": 7, "ref": "3.7 Rate limiting & concurrency", "requires": "characterize sync vs 429s (not too frequent, not too slow regardless of ceiling); per-layer concurrency." },
        { "id": "E2E.PhaseB.3_8", "order": 8, "ref": "3.8 Resilience", "requires": "strategy rotation mid-sync; infinite-pagination stuck -> recovery (content-hash may break the loop); generic mid-process failure at any stage; grace handling maximizes useful data that still lands despite failures." }
      ],
      "evidence": "Per cell: NL statement of what was proven + JSON (scrubbed IntegrationGetRun payload, DB count rows, relevant progress.jsonl events) + pass/fail. Every cell asserts OUTCOMES (ground-truth counts, second-layer non-empty, structured SyncWarnings) — never Status='Success'."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2E.PhaseC",
      "order": 3,
      "phaseRef": "§4 Phase C — Value Handling",
      "tier": "T10",
      "applicability": "always",
      "dualDialect": false,
      "requires": "Records of different value types map and persist correctly without throwing.",
      "evidence": "NL + JSON per value-type case + pass/fail."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2E.GenAction",
